description:
My name is Grant. I talk to the spirits using white and or pink noise generated from my P.C or white noise generated by running the faucets in my house. I take those responses and use an Artificial Intelligence Software to filter out the white noise and leave behind only human speech.

Asking the spirits about the deaths of Lisanne Froon and Kris Kremers from 2014.

I have created us our very own Reddit page! 
If you have a suggestion for a video or you want me to ask the spirits a question, go to the address and leave a post. No promises, but at least it will be saved here for me to go through!!

https://www.reddit.com/r/OptimalFrequency/

If you appreciate the research I am conducting and want to donate to Optimal Frequency, there is a small donate button on the YouTube banner (right side). I appreciate your support!

https://www.paypal.com/donate?hosted_button_id=L7JYMFK5ZVMWN

comments.text: Its hard to separate fact from fiction. There are oddities like Felicianos sway over the indigenous folks (who found the backpack) and his influence even in the town. Then theres the backpack. Wet and somewhat tattered maybe but in oddly good shape considering it was floating down a river for months during the rainy season. The fact that they did not find the girls on or near the trail must mean they were not lost on trail. Its a well used trail. Someone would have found them and it was well searched. The jungle wasnt, however. But, theres no way they would have, let alone could have, gotten far in the jungle I think. The way Ive heard it described, unless you have a machete, you really cant penetrate it and you cant go very far. Im not sure exactly of the terrain there or if theres some possible hidden precipice where they could have fallen and gotten stuck, but even then, I think someone would have heard them. They also never found the remnants of the help signals the girls had made that were featured in some of the (one of the?) night photos. I also found it odd that Kriss hair was dry and seemingly clean in the photo Lisanne took of the back of her head. I do not think Kris was dead in this photo. It looks too much like shes sat up and her hair isnt falling in a way to suggest shes lying down and theres no ground beneath her. Its possible they found a cave, but after a week in the jungle, I would think a girls bright blond hair would be absolutely filthy. Its just odd. Its as if they were on the trail and then poof ended up somewhere else where they must have KNOWN they couldnt use their phones very much and they realized that their calls would not go through so they didnt attempt more calls in that week or so that they were using their phones. Its just so weird they never found ANYTHING to show where they may have been except the remains and backpack. Nothing. That part is very odd. Then theres the story by the German man. Then there are the odd and contradictory stories by the villagers about when they saw the girls. Then theres that photo of those two boys and two girls which MAY have been of them, but its entirely possible its not. Perhaps two men scared them off trail and they ended up somewhat deep in the jungle? Lissanes bones DID show signs of excessive use ie: she walked for a very long time. And, again the jungle was not searched and I can only assume youd get very turned around in there and possibly slip and hurt yourself. Edit: I realize this is kind of unlikely because of what I said about the jungle, but its also the only reason/explanation for their not being on trail and not heading back the way they came when they realized they maybe had gone too far. Otherwise there could feasibly all sorts of foul play scenarios, but its hard to fathom when you have the night photos. They used flash how would their captors not see they were using it?
comments.author: @mr.b.3633
